@StayVeuntilBTS2025watch it and form your own opinion regardless if its bad. I wouldn't really advice adopting opinions on the internet just because you were told.


This anime isn't as bad as the comment you replied you said. Most of what he said ain't true, BUT there's still problems, and it didn't meet expectations

7-8/10 for me, watch it and form your own opinion instead of adopting mine, or the other guys opinion

@Halosrighthand I’ve completed all the games, I’ve beaten DMC 1 on hard mode currently trying DMD.

And I’m currently going mad trying to beat DMC 3 Vergil fight 3 Very hard mode ONLY using nevan, royal guard, Cerberus, Kalina Ann and ebony and ivory.

(Going insane, but I almost beat em last time🤣)

@benjaminmartin8554 That would be right... if dante wasn't recognized in the show to have also been fighting demons for years and having multiple jobs that he "left cuz got bored"... meaning he already is a badass with super human abilities... while Lady just has random tech that they conveniently made in the background to help her out.
It makes 0 sense for dante to whop everyone's ass in his apartment, dodge every single bullet so fast that he can pretend that he's shotting with the rest of the goons and just get blasted by lady later, over and over again... Does he have selective power that changes based on the enemy for some reason?
Dante's whole development doesn't even make sense if you consider all of that... he's just nerfed down whenever its convenient for the plot

@darkblasterzero4067 I almost entirely agree with you 
but even in DMC3 she's written "against" Dante at first but she doesnt take as much of the spotlight and in the end she trust him enough to join him and befriend him 

here "i get why" she betrays dante but the betrayal should have come from Baynes with a sniper for exemple not her necessarily
